*NOTE:* This suggestion is for {*}JIRA Cloud{*}. Using {*}JIRA Server{*}? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-12880].
{panel}
Sometimes it happens, that user comments on a Jira issue are not really related to the issue. 
We have such situations, when end users believe, that a problem they just discovered seems to be related but it's not. In such a case, it would be very helpful, if I could create a new issue with the comment as main problem description with a simple "click on a link".

Why not adding a "Create issue from this comment" link close to the "edit", "delete", "hide" links of the jira comment entries?

Currently, when searching for a string using the format "ABC-123" in Jira using the quick search, Jira will list the pre results as {*}key = ABC-123 OR text ~ "ABC-123"{*}, but if we press enter Jira will try to open the issue "ABC-123" and would not return the pre results listed previously.

If the issue doesn't exist, the message "You don't have access to this issue. Make sure the issue exists in this project. If it does, ask a project admin for permission to see the project's issues." is returned, but the issues that have the "ABC-123" in their summary won't be returned.

It would be good to have the correspondent result as shown when typing the string in the quick search.
{code:java}
key = ABC-123 OR text ~ "ABC-123"{code}
!JAC_.png!
